  "description": [
    "t ALL SIGNS POINT TO PROSPEROUS STATE Smaller Crops Will Affect Export Trade but Other Conditions Are Gratifying Globe Special Washington Service 1417 G Street WASHINGTON D C Nov 17The statistical returns received by the gov ernment from many sources have late ly been scanned with special interest with a view of determining the outlook for continued business prosperity So far as the current accounts of the rnited States treasury are concerned the condition is somewhat embarrass ing to the administration but the fact that the expenditures are daily exceed ing the receipts does not mean that the country is less prosperous than it was a year ago when there was a big treasury surplus The crop reports of the department of agriculture have not yet given ac curate returns of the wheat and corn crops but it is generally agreed that both crops are smaller than those of 1902 This condition will affect the ex port trade and will affect the pros perity of some of the farmers but the falling off in the production of these staples of the agricultural states is not very great There is a short oat crop this year however the product being estimated"
  ],
